<headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 01 at 10:39AM EDT  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...Thunderstorms will impact portions of Monroe, Wayne, Lenawee and
Washtenaw Counties through NOON EDT...
At 1036 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a line of thunderstorm
near Morenci, moving northeast at 55 mph.
HAZARD...Winds up to 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
This strong thunderstorm will be near...
Adrian around 1045 AM EDT.
Blissfield around 1055 AM EDT.
Petersburg, Deerfield and Britton around 1100 AM EDT.
Dundee around 1105 AM EDT.
Other locations impacted by this storm include Melvindale, Gibraltar,
Hudson Mills Metropark, Erie, Stony Point, Ridgeway, Sand Creek,
Samaria, Azalia and Medina.
People attending Michigan Stadium should seek safe shelter
immediately!
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
